title: Labor Turnover, Discharge Rate, Manufacturing for United States
notes:
Series Is Presented Here As Two Variables--(1)--Original Data, 1919-1930 (2)--Original Data, 1930-1958. Data Were Published As Annual Equivalents And Were Here Converted To Represent Monthly Rates By Dividing By 11.77; 12.17; 13.04; 12.62 Depending On If A Given Month Has 31, 30, 28, Or 29 Days (See Source, June, 1931, P. 127). Source: Bureau Of Labor Statistics, Monthly Labor Review, July, 1929 And February, 1931.

This NBER data series m08253a appears on the NBER website in Chapter 8 at http://www.nber.org/databases/macrohistory/contents/chapter08.html.
